  "local_port": 57842,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Does a user always need to keep the data \u2018ON\u2019 for outgoing/incoming calls on Jio network?",
  "response": "On the Jio network, voice calls are primarily handled through **VoLTE (Voice over LTE)** technology. VoLTE allows for high-quality voice calls over the 4G LTE data network, providing clearer audio and faster call setup times compared to traditional circuit-switched networks.\n\n**Regarding your question:**\n\n- **Data \"ON\" Requirement:**  \n  Generally, you **do not need to keep your mobile data actively turned on** (i.e., actively using data for browsing, apps, etc.) to make or receive voice calls on the Jio network. VoLTE operates independently to facilitate voice calls even when your data usage is not actively engaged.\n\n- **Device Settings:**  \n  However, it's essential to ensure that **VoLTE is enabled** in your smartphone's settings. Without VoLTE enabled, your device might default to older network technologies (like 2G or 3G) for voice calls, which might not be as efficient or high-quality.\n\n  **To check and enable VoLTE:**\n  1. **For Android Devices:**\n     - Go to **Settings** > **Network & Internet** > **Mobile Network**.\n     - Look for the **VoLTE** or **Enhanced 4G LTE Mode** option and ensure it's toggled **on**.\n  \n  2. **For iOS Devices:**\n     - Navigate to **Settings** > **Cellular** > **Cellular Data Options** > **Voice & Data**.\n     - Select **LTE, VoLTE On**.\n\n- **Potential Exceptions:**\n  - **Over Wi-Fi Calling:** If you're using Wi-Fi Calling instead of VoLTE, then having a stable internet connection (either Wi-Fi or mobile data) becomes crucial for call functionality.\n  - **Network Conditions:** In areas with poor LTE coverage, your device might switch to older network types, which could behave differently regarding data requirements.\n\n- **Power Consumption Consideration:**  \n  Keeping mobile data turned on doesn't significantly drain your battery solely for call purposes, especially if you're not actively using data-intensive applications. However, if you're concerned about battery usage, you can manage your app permissions and background data usage to optimize power consumption.\n\n**In summary:**\nFor standard voice calls on the Jio network using VoLTE, you **do not need to keep your mobile data actively turned on**. Ensure that VoLTE is enabled in your device settings to enjoy seamless and high-quality voice call experiences.\n\nIf you experience any issues with making or receiving calls without mobile data enabled, consider reaching out to Jio's customer support or checking for any device-specific settings that might affect VoLTE functionality.",
